  "prompt": "How many supercomputers are there in iit kharagpur?",
  "response": "As of my knowledge cutoff in October 2023, the exact number of supercomputers at the Indian Institute of Technology Kharagpur (IIT Kharagpur) isn't publicly specified. However, IIT Kharagpur is known to have robust High-Performance Computing (HPC) facilities that support a wide range of research activities across various departments.\n\n### High-Performance Computing at IIT Kharagpur\n\n1. **Computing Clusters:** IIT Kharagpur maintains several computing clusters that cater to different research needs. These clusters are equipped with powerful processors, large memory capacities, and high-speed interconnects to handle complex computational tasks.\n\n2. **Collaborative Initiatives:** The institute often collaborates with national initiatives like the Centre for Development of Advanced Computing (C-DAC) to access and utilize advanced computing resources.\n\n3. **Research Projects:** Various research projects in fields such as engineering, data science, artificial intelligence, and computational biology leverage HPC facilities at IIT Kharagpur to perform large-scale simulations, data analysis, and modeling.\n\n### Recommendations for Updated Information\n\n- **Official Website:** For the most accurate and up-to-date information, I recommend visiting the [IIT Kharagpur official website](https://www.iitkgp.ac.in/) or contacting their IT or HPC department directly.\n  \n- **Contacting Departments:** Reaching out to specific departments or research centers within IIT Kharagpur can provide more detailed insights into the available computing resources, including any supercomputing facilities.\n\n- **Recent Publications:** Reviewing recent research publications from IIT Kharagpur may also shed light on the computational resources utilized, as authors often acknowledge the infrastructure that supported their work.\n\nIf you have specific requirements or need detailed specifications about their HPC facilities, contacting IIT Kharagpur directly would be the most effective approach.",
